This paper deals with path loss estimation in femtocell networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves statistical analysis and signal processing, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia (cs.MM). The proposed method involves adaptive modulation and coding, which is related to system engineering (cs.SY). Finally, the paper deals with interference reduction, which is related to cryptography and security (cs.CR).
